geloto lemat 20-Mar-22 06:20 PM
Awesome. He takes out his small notebook/journal which he did technically canonically have even though it never came up. He glances through the pages of reminders, research notes, various miscellanies. He remembers the few times he had to compose music with vocal accompaniment; the art of the written word. He reaches the first blank page. Geloto reminisces over the past few weeks. Over the majority of his life, maybe. He thinks of Bruum; hopeless idealist, only able to understand when it was too late. Elfbat, ruthless idealist, yet held back by personal conflict. Jean Greyerl; a footnote of history, who died for nothing. The fascist, the family man, the fallen scenario. Madakoe, and what things he did seem to have a solid grasp on. The people who asked him questions, who showed him how pathetic he could be. He thinks of Femata Magus. He may have spent more time with her than most others, and he still wondered if he ever knew her. She was singleminded in her focus on survival, so when that failed, she left nothing behind. Her body and name were both commandeered by others. Will anyone remember her? Does she have anything left, after she stops being herself? Geloto thinks about himself and the world he inhabits. The agony of ignorance, of perpetually having his life upended by a whim of fate, of never knowing what or who or when he is. Of the same things, victories and tragedies and all, recurring for an unlimited amount of time even with people actively trying to stop it. Nobody learns from the mistakes of the past, communicates their knowledge and thoughts and feelings properly. How can he be certain this has really ended? Arcadius is taking power after Nero is defeated. Isn't that how it always goes? Can we be sure? "I'll make it certain." Geloto mutters to no one in particular in this isolated space. He'd seek a more permanent dwelling in time, but his neurons were firing obsessively right now, and he wanted to make sure he didn't forget anything.
My name is Geloto LeMat. As good a start as any. I am a musician, a political activist, a poet, a researcher, an author, and a member of high society. I have taken plenty of roles, possibly many I'm not even aware of. I have been blessed with unusual longevity, and I know the answers to many things others could only dream of. Until now. For all the beauty in people, there is twice as much (change to equal? reads as too neg) ugliness and hatred. They repeat the mistakes of their forefathers. Someone must make a record of their folly and triumphs to be examined. That someone is me. It is a heavy responsibility to be charged with creating this story, of having the ability to control what the future knows, but I guarantee I will relay it authentically and without bias. The following is gathered from my own personal experience, verification from and accounts of others ranging over a span of thousands of years, whatever historical record or reliable testimony could be located, and current scientific understanding. A Complete History Of ...of what? "The Loop"? No, that sounds stupid, and it would be better to hook people in and then explain the nature of that as an exciting midpoint reveal. People can't stand being bored. Of Q&A? That's basically meaningless. How many people does this involve? How many different nations with different names over different eras? I can't just call it the history of "everything", Geloto thinks. It doesn't really matter. It can be changed later. There will be plenty of time, going over such a breadth and juggling whatever else might happen to him. Inspiration strikes, and Geloto crosses out what he had, writes down a title, and scrambles to write down as much as he can in a mad frenzy, as if possessed. The Tale of Geloto LeMat (ft others) (edited)
